third_party/evi/ — libevi_crypto redistribution (Pattern C)
============================================================

This tree ships prebuilt libevi_crypto libraries + C++ headers alongside the
Go source so that `go get github.com/CryptoLabInc/envector-go-sdk` plus
`-tags libevi` can build the capture path without any external C++ toolchain
on the consumer side.

Expected layout
---------------
  third_party/evi/
    include/                      # C++ headers: deb/Encryptor.hpp, Context.hpp, Types.hpp, ...
    darwin_arm64/lib/libevi_crypto.{a,dylib}
    darwin_amd64/lib/libevi_crypto.{a,dylib}
    linux_amd64/lib/libevi_crypto.{a,so}
    linux_arm64/lib/libevi_crypto.{a,so}

Source of truth
---------------
  Upstream repo : github.com/CryptoLabInc/evi-crypto   (public)
  Pinned commit : TBD — fill in when first binary set is committed
  Build command : scripts/refresh-evi.sh

How to refresh
--------------
1. Clone or update CryptoLabInc/evi-crypto locally.
2. Run `scripts/refresh-evi.sh <path-to-evi-crypto-checkout>` from the repo root.
3. The script cmake-builds for each supported target and copies the resulting
   libs + headers into this tree.
4. Update the "Pinned commit" line above with the evi-crypto commit hash.
5. Commit the changed binaries + this file in the same PR.

Cross-compile escape hatch
--------------------------
Builds without `-tags libevi` use the pure-Go stubs in internal/crypto/ and
do not require any file in this tree. That path is how CI cross-compiles for
platforms we have not yet produced binaries for.

